parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent disconnection of the trailer brakes can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: The "Check Trailer Wiring" or "Trailer Brakes Disconnected" warning message appears on the dashboard
the trailer brakes do not engage
and the system reconnects and disconnects repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning instrument cluster can cause loss of critical information, such as speed, warnings, and gauges, which can lead to accidents and safety risks.
symptoms: The instrument cluster screen blinks on and off
displaying "Service Instrument Cluster" messages
and all indications of speed
warnings
and gauges are lost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning turn signal can cause confusion and accidents, especially when the hyperflash feature is activated.
symptoms: The "Check Right Front Turn Lamp" or "Check Left Front Turn Lamp" warning message appears
and the turn signal goes into hyperflash mode
rendering it non-functional.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The software and computer system issues can cause various malfunctions, including loss of communication with other components, which can lead to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: The main computer system loses communication with other components
the brake system control module loses communication
and the engine control module loses communication.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the trailer brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations while towing a trailer.
symptoms: The trailer brake system randomly connects and disconnects
the "Check Trailer Wiring" message appears on the instrument panel
the "Trailer Brakes Connected" and "Trailer Brakes Disconnected" messages display frequently
the brake pedal is depressed but the brakes fail to function
the vehicle experiences a sudden jolt or skid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the trailer brake controller can cause the loss of trailer brakes while towing, leading to a high risk of accidents and potential harm to the driver, passengers, and other road users.
symptoms: The trailer brake controller fails to recognize the trailer
the trailer brakes disconnect and reconnect intermittently
the truck travels at high speeds without trailer brakes
the system displays error messages or warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the computer/ECU can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine fails to start
the dashboard displays error messages or warning lights
the vehicle is unable to move
the battery is drained
and multiple systems fail simultaneously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The issues with the Android Auto/infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, reduce the functionality of the system, and pose concerns in states with hands-free device laws.
symptoms: The system reduces the A/C output when connected to Android Auto
incoming messages are not played
the system states that no active subscription is enabled
the system does not allow full functionality of Android Auto.
